1
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:06,600
The one who is
most dear to Kṛṣṇa.

2
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:12,320
Still, we could say,
“Well, that’s a general thing.

3
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:14,700
It’s not filling in the blank.”

4
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:18,300
[Guru | Closer Examination]

5
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:21,960
And as connotation increases,
denotation decreases.

6
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:26,090
—Oh, so we are being told here
the general principle,

7
00:00:26,090 --> 00:00:30,390
that we’ll think of our guru
as being most dear to Kṛṣṇa.

8
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:32,910
The Vaiṣṇava‒sresta—
the best of the Vaiṣṇavas,

9
00:00:32,910 --> 00:00:38,000
we’ve approached 
to take shelter of as guru,
 

10
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,000
and it is
we will think of

11
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,700
our guru is the one
who’s most dear to Kṛṣṇa,

12
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:46,000
as indicated by
Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī,

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:50,020
echoed by
Viśvanāth Cakravartī Ṭhākur.

14
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:51,600
He says

15
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:56,900
kintu prabhor yaḥ priya eva tasya
vande guroḥ śrī-caraṇāravindam
 

16
00:00:56,900 --> 00:01:01,100
where in the beginning
of that śloka, and it says

17
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:06,100
sākṣād‒hari‒tvena samasta‒śāstrair
uktas tathā bhāvyata eva sadbhiḥ

18
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:12,110
The scriptures are telling us—
see guru is Kṛṣṇa.

19
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:18,600
‘kintu’ means here,
but upon closer examination

20
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,700
‘su–samīkṣā’—
greater scrutiny.

21
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:28,700
If we are following that thread 
of Kṛṣṇa conception, of guru as Kṛṣṇa,

22
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:30,650
he’s saying,
“If we look deeper,

23
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:34,200
we’ll see—
kintu prabhor priya.

24
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,670
Guru is really 
prabhor priya,

25
00:01:36,670 --> 00:01:38,500
the one who is 
most dear to Kṛṣṇa.

26
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:44,630
So, if guru is seen …
we say—

27
00:01:44,630 --> 00:01:49,300
see Kṛṣṇa with greater,
a more refined way of seeing,

28
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:52,300
and you’ll see prabhor priya—
the one who is most dear to Kṛṣṇa.

29
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,300
Of all of those 
who are most dear to Kṛṣṇa

30
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:57,300
that means Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

31
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:00,400
What did Saraswatī Ṭhākur  
say at the conclusion

32
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:04,900
of the Caitanya-caritāmṛta’s purport?

33
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:09,790
—If I look deeply,
with greater depth of vision,

34
00:02:09,790 --> 00:02:13,600
depth of field, 
infinite depth of field

35
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:18,300
at Bhakti Vinod 􏰅Ṭhākur,
and Gaurakiśor dās Bābājī Mahārāj,

36
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:24,000
I see Gadādhar Paṇḍit,
and Svarūp Dāmodar,

37
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,900
or ultimately—
Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

38
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:31,460
I see my guru as
Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

39
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:35,500
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

